sequenceDiagram
    participant User
    participant Dispatcher as Dispatcher
    participant JiraLib as JIRA Python Library
    participant Goose as Goose CLI
    participant Recipe as Plan Recipe
    participant ACLI as JIRA CLI (acli)
    participant FileSystem as File System
    participant LLM as Azure GPT-4<br/>(via LiteLLM)
    participant Validator as WorkPlan Validator
    participant SQLite as SQLite DB
    participant Formatter as WorkPlan Formatter

    User->>Dispatcher: dispatcher run --ticket {ticket_key}
    
    rect rgb(230, 230, 255)
        Note over Dispatcher,SQLite: Step 1: Initialize Workflow
        Dispatcher->>JiraLib: Fetch ticket via JIRA API
        JiraLib-->>Dispatcher: JiraTicket<br/>(key, title, description, labels, status)
        Dispatcher->>SQLite: Check for duplicate workflows
        SQLite-->>Dispatcher: No active workflows
        Dispatcher->>SQLite: create_workflow()<br/>status: PENDING
        SQLite-->>Dispatcher: workflow_id
    end
    
    Dispatcher->>Goose: Run plan recipe with params<br/>(ticket_key, output_path)
    Goose->>Recipe: Initialize recipe
    
    rect rgb(230, 240, 255)
        Note over Recipe,ACLI: Step 2: Fetch JIRA Ticket (Recipe)
        Recipe->>ACLI: acli jira workitem view {ticket_key}
        ACLI-->>Recipe: Ticket details<br/>(summary, description, status)
    end
    
    rect rgb(240, 255, 240)
        Note over Recipe,FileSystem: Step 3: Analyze Repository
        Recipe->>FileSystem: Read README.md
        FileSystem-->>Recipe: Project structure
        Recipe->>FileSystem: List directories<br/>(dispatcher/, schemas/, state/)
        FileSystem-->>Recipe: File tree
        Recipe->>FileSystem: Read relevant files<br/>(patterns, conventions)
        FileSystem-->>Recipe: Code context
    end
    
    rect rgb(255, 245, 230)
        Note over Recipe,LLM: Step 4: Generate WorkPlan
        Recipe->>LLM: Generate WorkPlan JSON<br/>(ticket + repo analysis)
        LLM-->>Recipe: WorkPlan JSON draft
    end
    
    rect rgb(255, 240, 245)
        Note over Recipe,Validator: Step 5: Validate in Recipe (Retry Loop)
        loop Max 3 attempts
            Recipe->>FileSystem: Write to /tmp/workplan_temp.json
            Recipe->>Validator: python work_plan_validator.py
            alt Validation Passes
                Validator-->>Recipe: ✅ Validation passed
                Note over Recipe: Exit retry loop
            else Validation Fails
                Validator-->>Recipe: ❌ Error: {specific issue}
                Recipe->>LLM: Fix specific issue<br/>(e.g., add missing field)
                LLM-->>Recipe: Corrected WorkPlan JSON
            end
        end
    end
    
    rect rgb(240, 255, 255)
        Note over Recipe,FileSystem: Step 6: Write to File
        Recipe->>FileSystem: mkdir -p {output_dir}
        Recipe->>FileSystem: Write validated JSON<br/>to {output_path}
        FileSystem-->>Recipe: File created
        Recipe->>FileSystem: Verify file exists
        FileSystem-->>Recipe: ✅ Confirmed
    end
    
    Recipe->>Goose: ✅ WorkPlan generated
    Goose->>Dispatcher: WorkPlan JSON returned
    
    rect rgb(255, 250, 230)
        Note over Dispatcher,Validator: Step 7: Dispatcher Validates WorkPlan
        Dispatcher->>Validator: validate_work_plan(work_plan_data)
        alt Validation Passes
            Validator-->>Dispatcher: ✅ WorkPlan valid
            alt Status is "blocked"
                Note over Dispatcher: ❌ Mark workflow FAILED<br/>Cannot proceed
            end
        else Validation Fails
            Validator-->>Dispatcher: ❌ WorkPlanValidationError
            Note over Dispatcher: Mark workflow FAILED
        end
    end
    
    rect rgb(255, 235, 245)
        Note over Dispatcher,SQLite: Step 8: Store WorkPlan (AOS-39)
        Dispatcher->>SQLite: update_work_plan()<br/>Store WorkPlan JSON
        SQLite-->>Dispatcher: ✅ Stored
    end
    
    rect rgb(245, 235, 255)
        Note over Dispatcher,ACLI: Step 9: Post to Jira (AOS-39)
        Dispatcher->>Formatter: format_work_plan_comment()<br/>(WorkPlan, ticket_key)
        Formatter-->>Dispatcher: Formatted comment<br/>(summary, tasks, risks, approval)
        Dispatcher->>ACLI: acli jira workitem comment add<br/>--key {ticket_key}<br/>--comment {formatted_comment}
        alt Comment Posted Successfully
            ACLI-->>Dispatcher: ✅ Comment added
            Note over Dispatcher: WorkPlan visible on Jira
        else Comment Posting Failed
            ACLI-->>Dispatcher: ❌ Posting failed
            Note over Dispatcher: Log error, continue<br/>(WorkPlan still in SQLite)
        end
    end
    
    Dispatcher->>User: ✅ WorkPlan generated and posted<br/>View at: {jira_url}/browse/{ticket_key}
    
    Note over User,Formatter: WorkPlan Status Classification:<br/>• "pass" - Clear scope, ready to implement<br/>• "concerns" - Has risks or dependencies<br/>• "blocked" - Missing info or ambiguous<br/><br/>WorkPlan Comment Sections:<br/>• Plan Summary (approach and status)<br/>• Task List (with files affected)<br/>• Risks<br/>• Questions for Reviewer<br/>• Approval Instructions<br/>  - dispatcher approve {ticket_key}<br/>  - dispatcher reject {ticket_key}
